version.name: Tone Defeat
version.description: Its reggae time and if your supplies of dub are running low you can refuel at the latest Tone Defeat, featuring Kingtide, Sticky Fingers and Reverse Polarites, Massema, and the Domestics. Pre-book for a free house drink on entry and it's happy hour from 5-8pm.

version.name: Comedy on the Rox
version.description: Chris Radburn headlines, Billy Freeman supports, and MC Matt Elsbury keeps the night on the rails.

version.name: Powderfinger - Sunsets tour
version.description: It's their last ever tour, everyone - after 20 years Powderfinger ride off into the Sunsets (see what we did there) for the final time. Their pals Jet are also on the bill.

version.name: Celtic Woman
version.description: For the first time ever, the multi-platinum Irish singing sensations (ocalists Lisa Kelly, Chloë Agnew, Lynn Hilary, Alex Sharpe and fiddler Máiréad Nesbitt) play the nation's stadia in support of Songs from the Heart.

version.name: Splendour In The Grass 2010
version.description:
The Splendour In The Grass 2010 lineup has been announced. A bunch of acts have been on the rumour lists for weeks – like The Strokes, Mumford and Sons, The Pixies and The Temper Trap – but there are plenty of surprises too.
This year Splendour In The Grass is moving to the Woodford site in Queensland. It’s a bigger space, which means more live acts than ever.
